A vintage 1970s-era computer room scene rendered in warm sepia and faded orange tones, featuring an old IBM mainframe with spinning tape reels in the background. In the foreground, a wooden desk holds scattered punch cards, a worn programming manual, and a steaming coffee cup. Through a large window, a futuristic cityscape with modern glass towers is visible, creating a visual bridge between eras. The composition shows a winding path made of glowing code symbols flowing from the old mainframe, through the window, and transforming into modern mobile devices and sleek tablets in the distance. Dust motes float in warm afternoon light streaming through venetian blinds, casting striped shadows across the scene. The mood is nostalgic yet forward-looking, capturing the journey of technological evolution and continuous learning.
